1
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:05,760
Come on, sit down, what did I want to tell you?
-How should I know, babe?

2
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:08,480
I still can't read your mind.

3
00:00:09,040 --> 00:00:10,080
How do you call it?

4
00:00:10,160 --> 00:00:11,880
The thoughts.
-Funny.

5
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:14,080
It made me laugh, what do you want?

6
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:15,480
Come on, I wanted to tell you something.

7
00:00:15,560 --> 00:00:18,440
Fine, dude, so I guess it’s not that important.
-What an idiot I am.

8
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:21,880
Stop, don’t say idiot in front of the girls,
they’ll think that’s what you are.

9
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:23,840
Oh, I remembered.

10
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:25,520
Anyway, it wasn’t that important.

11
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:26,600
Come on, what, now you’re gonna tell me.

12
00:00:26,680 --> 00:00:28,760
No, I think my parents
had their anniversary this week.

13
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:30,680
What do you mean "think"? Why do you think?

14
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:33,320
Because my mom told me on Shabbat
that it would be or something like that,

15
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:34,920
No big deal, it’s just saying congratulations.

16
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:37,800
Tell me, are you normal?
I didn’t buy anything, why didn’t you tell me?

17
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:39,200
What happened to you? It’s not a silver wedding,

18
00:00:39,280 --> 00:00:42,600
just a regular anniversary, nothing special,

19
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:43,880
no need for a gift.
-What does that have to do with it?

20
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:45,400
You know your mom will never forgive me for this.

21
00:00:45,480 --> 00:00:47,720
Babe, my mom has three sons,
she’s used to it,

22
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:49,760
she doesn’t even expect it, she says so herself.

23
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:52,640
Fine, but I’m a daughter and his wife
and she does expect it from me.

24
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,200
Because you’re a woman?
-Yeah.

25
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:56,280
So what are you really saying to me?

26
00:00:56,840 --> 00:00:58,360
Tell me, are you crazy?
-Yeah.

27
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:06,320
Look at me, look at me and...

28
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,600
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

29
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:20,400
Where have you been? I was really worried.

30
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:27,800
Riki, congratulations on the anniversary.
-Thanks, sweetheart.

31
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:29,600
Mom, congratulations.

32
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:34,600
And I booked a place for the four of us to celebrate the event

33
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:37,200
at the most popular restaurant in Tel Aviv.

34
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,440
Isn’t it a waste of money? You didn’t have to.

35
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:41,720
I thought so too, but...

36
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:45,080
Where’s the restaurant?
-Come on, it’s that philosopher guy from MasterChef.

37
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:46,120
The philosopher.

38
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,840
Oh, I love his place.

39
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:49,400
Shabbat Shalom.

40
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:52,000
Meet my baby.
-Oh my.

41
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:54,160
This is my brother and his wife.

42
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:56,600
Sit down.
-Shh, nice to meet you.

43
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:59,960
Baby is a serious name.
What does it mean, that you play the violin?

44
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:00,960
No.

45
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:03,800
Because that could’ve been funny.
Think about it, baby...

46
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:05,800
I play the viola.

47
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:07,280
What a beautiful bouquet, Riki.

48
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:12,160
I got it as a gift for our anniversary.
-Really lovely.

49
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:14,920
I have an artistic trick for arranging flowers.

50
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:18,200
There’s something really calming about this arrangement,

51
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:20,920
very round, very nice.

52
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:22,720
Feng Shui?

53
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,440
No, today it’s Tao.

54
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:28,160
You’ve probably heard of yin and yang
but not of wei wei wei.

55
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:29,880
Oh wei wei?

56
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:33,360
It means "doing without action" in Japanese.

57
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,680
I’d love it if you could bring me a bouquet like this on Wednesday.

58
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:39,840
Wednesday?
-Yeah, Wednesday is my birthday.

59
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:42,040
Did you forget that?
-Just kidding with you.

60
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,720
Of course not, what, could I forget something like that?

61
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:46,840
I already bought a kitchen and everything.
-Really?

62
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:49,600
Let’s just do it straight, it’ll be quicker.

63
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,040
Mom.
-And even sex.

64
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:53,280
Interesting.
-Sex with...

65
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:56,960
Mom, where are the flowers from?
-Where do you think?

66
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:58,720
You won’t believe what he did to me.

67
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,120
-Pinchas.

68
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,960
He took me on a flight over the country

69
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:05,440
with a picnic parking spot.
-Wow.

70
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:08,040
What a cool gift, that’s romantic.

71
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:11,840
I wouldn’t wish that on my enemies.

72
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:15,080
Where’s Dad?
-In the kitchen, looking for a marker.

73
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:17,840
So I’ll go say hi and ask where the bouquet’s from.

74
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:22,800
That sounds like an amazing gift, what is it?
-Do me a favor,

75
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:24,720
it was a nightmare.

76
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:28,480
I didn’t believe I’d survive
to tell you this. Sit down, sit down.

77
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:30,440
Hey, Dad.
-Hi, Shai, what’s up?

78
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,600
Want an egg?
-No, no.

79
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:33,400
No?
-No...

80
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,400
Listen, I messed up,

81
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:38,800
I just found out Shani has a birthday this week

82
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:39,880
and I have no idea what to get her.

83
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:43,520
Shai, relax, you didn’t mess up,
you’re not supposed to remember dates.

84
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,400
Chill out.

85
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:47,800
Your wife’s birthday?
-Not at all.

86
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,840
It’s her job to remind you,

87
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:50,800
you have enough on your plate,

88
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:53,160
you’ve got a family to support, a house to manage.

89
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:56,840
No, Dad, it’s 2011
so I’m not sure your theory holds up.

90
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,400
It’s not about theory or the year,

91
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:01,160
it’s about evolution and nature.

92
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,880
A man doesn’t have the gene to remember dates...

93
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:06,720
Yeah, yeah, we don’t have
access to that part of the brain.

94
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:08,600
And women do?

95
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:12,200
What do you think they did in the cave
while we were out hunting mammoths?

96
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:15,560
What?
-They sat and doodled on the walls of a calendar.

97
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:19,279
What, were there dates back then?
-They invented dates.

98
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:21,480
Look, this month, for example, like a cycle,

99
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,680
four weeks, 28 days.

100
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,680
I didn’t know that.

101
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:28,400
And how do you think I remembered
my wedding anniversary?

102
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:31,640
Did Mom remind you?
-She wrote it on my forehead in mirror writing.

103
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:34,200
So you took her on a flight over the country.

104
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:35,680
Yeah, so I could enjoy a bit too.

105
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:38,640
But what should I get her? Something for her, something for the house.

106
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:41,160
With your years of wisdom, you have no insight on this?

107
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:43,560
Whatever you bring will be wrong.

108
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:46,080
So how do I get out of this?
-Take her on a flight over the country,

109
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:50,120
an amazing, romantic experience,
Mom screamed the whole flight, it was something else.

110
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,760
No, no, I don’t think so.
-And the view from above...

111
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:56,520
What am I saying when you can see everything.
Look, we filmed everything,

112
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:59,160
our wedding anniversary on the ninth of... the year 5772.

113
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:02,160
No, no, I missed one thing, Shai.
-What?

114
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:05,880
I should’ve hired a photographer to capture
the nausea from the night after.

115
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:09,680
I was nauseous all night.

116
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,680
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

117
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:15,640
Where have you been? I was really worried.
-What were you worried about?

118
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:18,080
I know...

119
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:21,520
Don’t ask what Dad did to me.

120
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:24,480
No, don’t tell me he also
washed your dry cleaning in the machine.

121
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,520
Next time you get close to the washing machine.

122
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,880
Jerk.
-Trash.

123
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:32,560
What do you mean? He took her on a flight over the country.

124
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:35,240
What, did he win "Philobi"?
-I'm serious, babe.

125
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:40,360
What do you mean? That's my gift for our anniversary.

126
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:42,800
Come on, when did you have it?
-This week.

127
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:44,960
Not on purpose. Itamar, I'm dying here.

128
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:49,200
It's fine, I don't expect Mambo
to remember stuff like that.

129
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,920
Why didn't you remind me, babe?
-What?

130
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,000
So, when are we eating?
Is there schnitzel? I'm going to grab some.

131
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:57,400
Babe, don't fill up,
just a reminder we have another dinner today.

132
00:05:57,960 --> 00:05:58,840
I remember, I remember.

133
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,160
Come on, so what happened?

134
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,200
What?

135
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:04,240
Long story short...

136
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:08,080
Mom, just a reminder we've heard this story already.

137
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:12,280
Yeah, but you haven't heard how Dad came
and told me he has a surprise

138
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,800
and that I shouldn't eat anything.

139
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:16,560
Yeah, but you told that, Riki.

140
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:18,560
Yeah, but Michal didn't hear.
-I didn't hear.

141
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:22,320
I thought he was going to
surprise me with medical tests,

142
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,280
otherwise, why fast?
-Why indeed?

143
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:27,800
Buy her some jewelry.
-Jewelry?

144
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,000
Why is everyone swimming in money like you?

145
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:31,120
I'm telling you, take her on a flight in the sky.

146
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:34,320
Come on, come see how beautiful this is,
I'm going to put it on DVD.

147
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:36,640
Dad, Dad, not a word to Shani, okay?
Because she doesn't know anything.

148
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,560
Of course.

149
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:40,280
What's the rush? You finished the schnitzels.

150
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,200
Michal is dragging me to dinner at her friends' place.

151
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:44,000
Not fun.
-No.

152
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:45,520
I hate her friends,

153
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,200
a bunch of freeloaders.

154
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:49,880
Living together in some room, five roommates.

155
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:52,720
A filthy room where just sitting there
you could catch a disease.

156
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:56,200
They're all vegetarians, only eating the food
they grow

157
00:06:56,600 --> 00:07:00,200
in the 'filthy room,
you get what I mean?

158
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:02,560
What’s going on? Where are you?
Why are you leaving me there alone?

159
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,240
Can I have a schnitzel?
-Take one, here.

160
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:09,240
So, who’s that girl?
-Flute girl.

161
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:11,800
Like a flute.
-Like a flute. Wiping in its shade.

162
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:13,160
And viola.

163
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:14,400
Really?

164
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:16,880
Cute.
-Yeah, yeah.

165
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:20,360
I've been with her for two days.
-Right.

166
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,680
And it's serious.
-Yeah.

167
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:24,560
Until now, we've only hung out at my place,

168
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:27,040
but she wants to go out today,
I have no idea where to take her.

169
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:28,040
You know, she's a bit...

170
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:30,840
What, flexible?
-What, makes a lot of noise?

171
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:34,800
Also. But no, I meant she's...

172
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:38,440
A hipster from Tel Aviv.
-Hip...

173
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,440
What's a hipster?

174
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:43,760
Is it related to the trio?
-No, no, come on.

175
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:47,640
What you used to call a philosophical Tel Aviv girl.

176
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,200
Honestly, I'm disappointed.

177
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:55,800
I had nausea all night.

178
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,800
That's it, it's ready. Where are the boys?

179
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:03,680
Shaiko, Tamari, Adamkia,
come see the horror movie.

180
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:05,080
Why like that, Riki?

181
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:07,200
I wasn't wearing makeup, I didn't know they were filming,

182
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,440
Seriously, Mom.

183
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:11,240
Come on, we're here, let’s go.

184
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:15,480
So, as you already know
I planned a surprise for Mom.

185
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,400
We know-
-we know-

186
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,320
We know.

187
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:19,680
What I'm telling you now happened before the movie.

188
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:24,440
Early in the morning, I covered her eyes
and drove her in the car.

189
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:27,280
I sat the whole way, it was great.
-Yeah.

190
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:30,960
On the way, she told me she didn't do an enema.

191
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:35,919
He told me to fast, I thought
we were going for a colonoscopy.

192
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:38,559
In hindsight, I regret we didn't do it.

193
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:42,840
Then we got to the airport,
I took off her eye cover...

194
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,760
Here you go.

195
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,240
Press it.
-I'm pressing.

196
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:52,040
Press it.
-I pressed.

197
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:53,960
Oh, it's starting.

198
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,880
That's it, Riki, you can take off the scarf.

199
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,640
Huh? Huh?

200
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,720
Pinchas, where did you bring me?

201
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:05,840
Riki, I know you think I forgot

202
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:06,960
but I didn't forget,

203
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:11,000
how could I forget that 43 years ago...
-2, 42.

204
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:13,000
Where did you bring me, Pinchas?

205
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:15,800
Like the cooking holiday of old,
that was full of joy,

206
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:18,200
that's how I want to lift you up.
-What?

207
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:20,440
Pinchas, where did you bring me?

208
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:24,600
Riki, I want to lift you up
high to the sky like my love for you.

209
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:27,520
How sweet.
-Meet Omram, our photographer and pilot.

210
00:09:27,920 --> 00:09:28,800
Oh wow.

211
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:33,240
Where did you bring me? Why didn't you tell me they were filming?

212
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:36,440
Right, Pinchas, it's so romantic, it's lovely.

213
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:38,600
Now I understand why you felt nauseous, Mom.

214
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:41,600
Looks nice, Dad.
-Right, it's stunning, Pinchas.

215
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:43,080
Really beautiful, Dad, good job.

216
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:47,280
It would have been nice if you guys! Now
turn around and go home.

217
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:49,320
But that's where the nightmare began.

218
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:58,080
For an hour, I was stuck
in a matchbox in the air.

219
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:01,560
Good thing our country is tiny, I'm telling you,

220
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:03,360
Give more back to the Palestinians.

221
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:06,320
Here comes the takeoff.

222
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:10,240
What's that noise?
-That's the engine noise.

223
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:12,080
Yeah, I forgot to tell you

224
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:15,240
that the engine was with us in the matchbox.

225
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:19,560
Pinchas, this thing is dangerous.

226
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:21,800
I told you: this is the perfect gift.

227
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:28,080
What is it, Mom, are you yelling or yawning?
-Both.

228
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:31,400
It was scary and boring at the same time.

229
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:35,400
Why boring? The view from up there was amazing,

230
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:37,080
it's a really interesting way to see

231
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:39,760
all the places you've been
in the last year from a bird's eye view.

232
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:42,840
Look, now we're passing
over Assaf Harofeh Hospital.

233
00:10:42,920 --> 00:10:44,240
Honey, with all due respect to your dad,

234
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,360
if you do something like this to me
I’ll look better than the plane.

235
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:48,000
I think I’ll jump myself.

236
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:53,600
Wow, I can't stand this music,

237
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:55,320
it's so '92.
-Right,

238
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,080
even though there's something about the combination of the engine noise

239
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,720
that makes it interesting, right?

240
